summary: Amazon's "Secret Level" anthology series has garnered mixed reactions. Some critics, like TheGamer, praise the Warhammer episode as the best 40K TV since "Astartes." Others, such as The Verge, criticize the series for its limited content, describing it as "a hollow anthology of video game cutscenes." PC Gamer provides an in-depth review of each episode, while Variety shares insights from the show's bosses on the scrapped "Concord" episode. Looper gives a negative review, calling the series "too many losers." The A.V. Club criticizes the show's focus on violence and gore, and IGN deems it "Console Bores." Rotten Tomatoes offers a summary of the series, while BBC.com highlights the show boss's perspective on fan reactions over critical reviews.

name: Mavericks vs Thunder
summary: The Oklahoma City Thunder will face off against the Dallas Mavericks in the NBA Cup quarterfinals. The game will be streamed live on CBS Sports and FuboTV. Shai Gilgeous-Alexander led the Thunder to victory over the Mavericks in the previous meeting, dominating Luka Dončić. The Mavericks and Thunder will be looking to advance to the semifinals. name: Kroger Albertsons merger
summary: Several courts have issued injunctions to block the planned merger between Kroger and Albertsons, two major grocery store chains. These rulings represent a setback for the companies' plans to combine their operations into a single entity. Federal and state courts have cited antitrust concerns as the reason for their decisions, expressing concerns that the merger could lead to reduced competition in the grocery industry and higher prices for consumers. The rulings may put the future of the merger in jeopardy, as the companies now face legal obstacles and increased scrutiny from regulators.

name: Mitch McConnell
summary: On Thursday, U.S. Senate Minority Leader Mitch McConnell suffered a fall during a Senate Republican lunch, resulting in minor injuries. McConnell, 82, received medical attention after the incident, with his deputy assuring that he was "fine." The fall, in which McConnell reportedly sprained his wrist and cut his face, occurred at the Capitol building and prompted a medical response. While the cause of the fall is unknown, it is noteworthy that McConnell previously experienced public freezing episodes over a year ago. Despite the incident, McConnell reportedly took an indirect swipe at former President Donald Trump regarding America's role in the world.
